{"name":"Improved Unarmed Strike [Combat]","type":"feat","img":"modules/greyhawk-pathfinder-1e/images/icons/featsfeatures/improvedUnarmedStrike.png","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.pf1.feats.2aTFNMs3pW6nUBlr"},"scene-packer":{"hash":"1efdaf1956f0bfa40b16e4e16f5346aa4d303904","sourceId":"Item.c3c9bJ1uGYECv51T"}},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>You are skilled at fighting while unarmed.</em></p><p><strong>Benefits<br></strong>You are considered to be armed even when unarmed—you do not provoke attacks of opportunity when you attack foes while unarmed. Your unarmed strikes can deal lethal or nonlethal damage, at your choice.</p><p><strong>Normal<br></strong>Without this feat, you are considered unarmed when attacking with an unarmed strike, and you can deal only nonlethal damage with such an attack.</p><hr><h3><strong>Combat Trick (from the Combat Stamina feat)</strong></h3><p><em><strong>Source</strong> Pathfinder Unchained pg. 124</em></p><p>When you deal nonlethal damage with an unarmed strike, you can spend up to 5 stamina points to deal an amount of additional nonlethal damage equal to double the amount of stamina points you spent.</p><p></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[["Combat"],["Unarmed"],["Offensive"]],"actions":[],"uses":{"per":"","value":0,"maxFormula":""},"attackNotes":[],"effectNotes":[],"changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"tag":"feat_improvedUnarmedStrike","useCustomTag":true,"armorProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"weaponProf":{"value":[],"custom":""},"languages":{"value":[],"custom":""},"flags":{"boolean":{},"dictionary":{"source":"PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 128","source_type":"feat"}},"scriptCalls":[],"featType":"feat","associations":{"classes":[]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","disabled":false,"classSkills":{"acr":false,"apr":false,"art":false,"blf":false,"clm